  · cFebdtrrSuanpouirmtynsgo o2re2cdf  ·
Iran's Atomic Energy Organization has published a statement about the quarterly agreement with the International Atomic Energy Agency, as well as the continuation of ′′ essential supervision ′′ of Iran's nuclear activities. At the same time, the Atomic Energy Organization announced that the agreement will be ′′ confidential ′′ and will not be published.
Last day, following the visit of Rafael Grosi, the Director General of the International Atomic Energy Agency to Iran, and on the verge of the Iranian parliament and the Agency reached a three-month agreement.
Now in the statement of the Iranian Atomic Energy Organization regarding the Iranian Memorandum to continue the ′′ essential ′′ supervision of the
′′ The intention of continuing the essential fact-testing and supervision in the statement section 2, as described in the agreement, is that for three months, Iran has recorded the information of some activities and equipment specified in the attachment. And he will keep to himself. In the meantime, the agency will have no access to this information and the information will remain exclusively with Iran. If sanctions were completely cancelled within three months, Iran will leave this information to the agency, otherwise the information will be erased forever."
However, the Iranian Atomic Energy Organization announced that it will not publish the agreement with the agency ′′ due to protective considerations ′′ about the country's nuclear facility.
